    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36a.62"/>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="italics">Mrs. William Watkins
                        <lb/>
                    209 College Avenue 
                        <lb/>
                    Swarthmore, Pa. 19081</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>October 16, 1972</dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>5835 Vine Street</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Lincoln, Neb.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt&#8212;</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Gov. Exon has suggested that I write to you for help in getting copies of your poems to read a group of poetry lovers here. Our local book store has been able to get me only one of your works, "Black Elk Speaks". Since we are a poetry study group, we would like to know where we may buy a copy of your lyrics and other poems. Some of us heard you on the Dick Cavett show several months ago and were much impressed by you and your explanations of the American Indian's culture.</p> 
                
                <p>Any help you can give on our problem will be deeply appreciated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Hilda K. Watkins</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">62</fw>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
